@NODE "intro" "What the heck is HLH?"


@{Shine "Introduction"}


@{b}HotListHandler@{ub} @{b}(HLH)@{ub} will manage your hotlist!


My goal was to share one hotlist with all the browsers available for the Amiga.


If you use more than one browser then use @{b}HotListHandler@{ub}.

If you stick with one browser, well, use it anyway.
@{LIndent 5}


@{u} @{b}Features@{ub} @{uu}
@{LIndent 10}

@{b}o@{ub} A nice toolbar

@{b}o@{ub} Easy to use

@{b}o@{ub} Supports many browsers

@{b}o@{ub} Share one hotlist with different browsers

@{b}o@{ub} Offers a QuickMenu for fastlinks

@{b}o@{ub} Creates an index when viewing the hotlist through a browser

@{b}o@{ub} Grab URL's from browsers (if the browser supports it via ARexx)

@{b}o@{ub} Edit the hotlist while off-line (create groups, add URL's, etc.)

@{b}o@{ub} Jump to any public screen

@{b}o@{ub} Totally font sensitive

@{b}o@{ub} And many more.....
@{LIndent 0}


@{Fhine "NEW"} @{u} @{b}Features in version 1.10@{ub} @{uu}
@{LIndent 10}

@{b}o@{ub} Search a Hotlist

@{b}o@{ub} Sort a Hotlist

@{b}o@{ub} HLH Toolbar Position Tooltypes

@{b}o@{ub} Print a Hotlist

@{b}o@{ub} Reload, Open, Load, and Save As menu items.

@{b}o@{ub} Support for the new Voyager, Voyager-NT

@{b}o@{ub} An ARexx port for program control
@{LIndent 0}


@{JCenter}
@{BG Fill}
 @{"Install" Link "install"} @{b}HLH@{ub} and see why it is so useful. 
@{JLeft}


@{BG Background}@{b}HotListHandler@{ub} is @{"Shareware" Link "register"}, but it is not crippled in any way.

   Please @{"Register" LINK "register"} if you are using it on a regular basis.

          It is only a @{"small fee" Link "register"} for @{"my" Link "author"} work.

@EndNode


@NODE "requirements" "What does HLH need to run?"


@{Shine "Requirements"}
@{LIndent 10}


You must be using @{b}Amiga@{ub} OS3.0+.


@{b}HLH@{ub} can run as 'stand alone,' so you can edit your hotlist offline.


You will find @{b}HLH@{ub} to be more
useful if you use a web browser ;-)
@{LIndent 0}


@{BG Fill}@{JCenter}

 You must @{"register" Link "register"} this software if you use it on a regular basis. 
@{BG Background}

@EndNode


