@NODE "install" "How to install HLH"
@TOC "MAIN"
@PREV "register"


@{Shine "Installation"}


@{JLeft}
  Nothing terribly difficult.

@{LIndent 5}

An Installer Script is provided to simplify your life.
@{Line}After all, that's what computers are supposed to be for!


The Installer Script will use your Amiga's Install program.



For those who are "Installer Impaired",
here is what the script will do :)@{LIndent 10}


Copy @{b}HotListHandler@{ub} to a convenient place on your drive.


Set the HOTLIST @{"ToolType" Link "tooltype"} in the icon if you like.


Run an ARexx script contained in the "Extras" drawer if it finds an @{u}AddToHotlist@{uu} hotlist
in your AWeb drawer.@{LIndent 5}



After running the Installer:@{LIndent 10}

Use Icon Edit to change other @{"ToolTypes" Link "tooltype"} as you see fit.@{LIndent 5}


See @{"usage" Link "usage"} to run @{b}HotListHandler@{ub}@{LIndent -5}



@{JCenter}
@{" Register " Link "register"} when you find that you cannot live without @{b}HLH@{ub}.@{LIndent 0}


@EndNode


@NODE "usage" "How to use HLH"
@TOC "MAIN"


@{Shine "Usage"}


@{JLeft}
@{b}HotListHandler@{ub} may be run from the Workbench or a CLI.

@{LIndent 5}

From WB, just double click on its icon.@{LIndent 10}

You can set some @{"tooltypes" LINK "tooltype"} in the icon.@{LIndent 5}


From the CLI, type the path (if necessary) and the name to start @{b}HLH@{ub}.@{LIndent 10}

You must specify a stack of at least 4096 bytes to successfully launch @{b}HLH.@{ub}

@{b}HLH@{ub} will also accept some CLI @{"arguments" LINK "tooltype"}.

Note that CLI arguments will override any tooltypes!@{LIndent 0}



When you start @{b}HLH@{ub} a @{"toolbar" Link "toolbar"} will open on the default or named
public screen.

If the pubscreen you have named is not open @{b}HLH@{ub} will open on the system
default pubscreen.@{LIndent 5}


Before the toolbar is opened @{b}HLH@{ub} will try to read a hotlist. @{b}HLH@{ub} can read AWeb's
hotlist format. It will use a similar format when saving, so AWeb can always display
the hotlist on it's own. Check the @{"browsers" Link "browsers"} page to see if the
browsers you use are supported by @{b}HLH@{ub}.@{LIndent 5}


@{"ARexx" Link "arexx"} can control HLH, so scripts can be written to support nearly any
Amiga program.


Use the toolbar to open the various @{b}HLH@{ub} @{"windows" Link "windows"}.


When any @{b}HLH@{ub} window is open you can access a @{"menu" Link "menu"}.@{LIndent 0}



When you see a URL you would like to add to your hotlist, open or move @{b}HLH@{ub} to the same
screen as your reader.
@{Line}It is then easy to grab or copy the link.

@EndNode "usage"


@Node "toolbar" "That funny looking thing at the top of your screen"
@TOC "usage"


@{Shine "Toolbar"}


When you start @{b}HotListHandler@{ub} a toolbar will open on the default public screen,
or, if you have set the tooltype and/or provided a CLI argument, on the specified
public screen. If the pubscreen you have named is not open @{b}HLH@{ub} will open on the default
pubscreen. See the @{"menu" Link "menu"} page for information on jumping to another pubscreen.@{LIndent 5}


Use the @{"ToolTypes" Link "tooltype"} to specify a position for the Toolbar.@{Fhine "NEW"}


The toolbar will adapt itself to the screenbar height and has five image buttons;
presented here from left to right.@{LIndent 10}



  @{Shyne "QUIT"} @{LIndent 15}
To quit @{b}HLH@{ub}, you will be warned if changes have not been saved.@{LIndent 10}


  @{Shyne "OPEN"} @{LIndent 15}
This button will open the @{"main window" Link "mainwindow"}.@{LIndent 10}


    @{Shyne "QM"} @{LIndent 15}
Open a @{"QuickMenu" Link "quickmenu"} for fastlinks.@{LIndent 10}


 @{Shyne "SHOW"} @{LIndent 15}
Tells the browser (if running) to show your hotlist. @{b}HLH@{ub} will also create an index for it.@{LIndent 10}


@{Shyne "QGRAB"} @{LIndent 15}
With@{LIndent 24} this button you QuickGrab a URL from a browser (if running and if
the @{"browser" Link "browsers"} supports it). If no other window of @{b}HLH@{ub} is open, or
no group is selected, the URLs are placed in a @{"buffer" Link "bufferwindow"}. Later
you can place these URLs in your hotlist.@{LIndent 10}






























@EndNode "toolbar"


@Node "arexx" "HLH ARexx Commands"
@TOC "usage"


@{Shine "ARexx"}@{Fhine "NEW"}


PortName = HLHANDLER
@{LIndent 0}


'addlink'@{LIndent 15} TITLE/A/K, URL/A/K, GROUP/K, QM/S@{LIndent 5}

Add a URL to the currently loaded hotlist.@{LIndent 15}

TITLE@{LIndent 20} is the name you wish to associate with the URL.@{LIndent 15}

URL@{LIndent 20} is the address of the page.@{LIndent 15}

GROUP@{LIndent 20} will add the URL to the named group.
If the specified group does not yet exist it will be created.

If GROUP is not specified, AddLink will function like the QuickGrab button.
The URL will be placed in the @{"buffer" Link "bufferwindow"}.@{LIndent 15}

QM@{LIndent 20} will add the URL to the QuickMenu @{b}only if@{ub}  a GROUP is named.@{LIndent 5}


Example:@{FG Fill}@{LIndent 20} addlink TITLE '"Robert's Homepage"' URL "http://www.tip.nl/users/robertn"
@{FG Text}@{LIndent 0}



'addgroup'@{LIndent 15} /K@{LIndent 5}

Add a new GROUP to the end of the current Hotlist.@{LIndent 5}


Examples:@{FG Fill}@{LIndent 20} addgroup "Companies"

addgroup '"Personal Homepages"'
@{FG Text}@{LIndent 0}



'hotlist'@{LIndent 15} LOAD/S, SAVE/S, FILE/K, FORCE/S@{LIndent 5}

Load or save a hotlist.@{LIndent 15}

LOAD @{LIndent 20} without a FILE argument will reload the hotlist.@{LIndent 15}

SAVE @{LIndent 20} will save the current hotlist.@{LIndent 15}

FILE @{LIndent 20} will LOAD or SAVE the named FILE.@{LIndent 15}

FORCE@{LIndent 20} will not bring up a requester even if you have made changes
to the hotlist. Any changes will be discarded.@{LIndent 5}


Examples:@{FG Fill}@{LIndent 20} hotlist LOAD FORCE

hotlist FILE "Work:Voyager/HLHandler.hotlist" SAVE
@{FG Text}@{LIndent 5}


NOTE:@{FG Fill}@{LIndent 15} The 'FILE' keyword works like the menu
options 'Save as...' & 'Open'. HLH will use this path and filename
the next time 'Load' or 'Save' are called.@{FG Text}@{LIndent 0}



'show'@{LIndent 5}

Displays the hotlist through the browser.@{LIndent 0}



'quit'@{LIndent 15} FORCE/S@{LIndent 5}

Quits HLH.@{LIndent 15}

FORCE@{LIndent 20} will not bring up a requester even if you have made changes
to the hotlist. All changes will be lost.@{LIndent 2}
@{LIndent 0}






























@EndNode "arexx"


@Node "windows" "HLH Windows"
@TOC "usage"
@Next "menu"


@{Shine "Windows"}


@{LIndent 5}

@{" Main Window " Link "mainwindow"} Access the Main Program.


@{" Quick Menu " Link "quickmenu"} To bounce to an often used web page.


@{" Edit Window " Link "editwindow"} Enhance and modify your HotList, edit your QuickMenu.


@{" Search Window " Link "searchwindow"} Search your HotList.@{Fhine "NEW"}


@{" Buffer " Link "bufferwindow"} Copies and Cuts are stored here.



@{" Menu " Link "menu"} Technnincally not a window, but, when an @{b}HLH@{ub} window is active,
you have access to this with the right mouse button.

@EndNode "windows"


@Node "mainwindow" "Where most of HLH's features are found"
@TOC "windows"


@{Shine "Main Window"}

@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "+="} @{LIndent 10)
This button will open the @{"buffer window" Link "bufferwindow"} (see also @{"QGRAB" Link "toolbar" 20}).@{LIndent 5}
@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Parent"}@{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 10}
Go to the parent group if you are in a subgroup.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Up & Down"} @{LIndent 10}
buttons in the main window will allow easy rearrangement of your hotlist.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Cut & Copy"} @{LIndent 10}
place a URL in the @{b}HLH@{ub} @{"buffer" Link "bufferwindow"}, allowing you to select a group,
or groups, to contain the URL.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Groups"} @{LIndent 10}
takes you up to the Hotlist Index.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Edit"} @{LIndent 10}
opens the @{"edit window" Link "editwindow"}.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "New"} @{LIndent 10}
will allow you to manually enter a URL.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Remove"} @{LIndent 10}
You can not get back what you have @{u}Removed@{uu}, the URL or group is lost after
clicking @{b}Remove@{ub}!@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Grab"} @{LIndent 10}
will grab the URL you are viewing and place it in the currently selected group.
If no group is selected the URL will be placed in the @{"buffer" Link "bufferwindow"}.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Search"}@{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 10}
Opens a @{"search" Link "searchwindow"} window.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Sort"}@{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 10}
@{"Sort" Link "sort"} Groups or URLs.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "About"} @{LIndent 10}
opens a standard Amiga requester.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Reload"}@{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 10}
Reload the hotlist, deleting any changes you have made.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Save"} @{LIndent 10}
to save your changes to disk.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Cancel"} @{LIndent 10}
to not save your changes.@{LIndent 5}

You can use a @{"Tooltype" Link "tooltype" 20} to have @{b}HLH@{ub} open
the MainWindow upon startup.@{Fhine "NEW"}

@EndNode "mainwindow"


@Node "quickmenu" "The Fast way to GoTo a URL"
@TOC "windows"


@{Shine "QuickMenu"}


QuickMenu (QM) is a small window containing URLs which you have chosen to be (you guessed it!)
quickly available, without having to go through the Groups in the Main Window or the browser's hotlist.


Clicking a name in the QuickMenu will tell the browser (if running) to go to this URL.


Remember it's a QuickMenu, one click on a URL is enough.


Click QM or the RMB to close this menu, or click another @{b}HLH@{ub} window to close the QuickMenu.


Select or unselect the QM box in the @{"edit window" Link "editwindow"} to control which URLs are
contained in the QM.

@EndNode "quickmenu"


@Node "editwindow" "How to modify your HotList"
@TOC "windows"


@{Shine "Edit Window"}


The Edit Window is reached from the @{"Main Window" Link "mainwindow"}.

The Edit Window is used to modify the Title or the URL, and to control the QuickMenu list.


Besides the standard Amiga gadgets the edit window has two text fields and four buttons.@{LIndent 5}



@{u} Text: @{uu}


@{Shyne "Title"} @{LIndent 10}
so you can change the title of the URL which has captured your interest. @{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "URL" @{LIndent 10}
will allow you to keep up with the rapid changes of home page addresses. @{LIndent 5}



@{u} Buttons: @{uu}


@{Shyne "QM"} @{LIndent 10}
will add or subtract this URL from your QuickMenu. @{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Accept"} @{LIndent 10}
will not close this window. This is very handy for adding new URL's or groups manually,
as well as setting up your QuickMenu. @{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Accept & Close"} @{LIndent 10}
will do as stated. @{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Cancel"} @{LIndent 10}
will also do as stated. @{LIndent 0}



Use the Main Window to SAVE your changes.

@EndNode "editwindow"


@Node "bufferwindow" "Where modifications are made"
@TOC "windows"


@{Shine "Buffer Window"}



The buffer window is accessed by opening the Main Window and clicking on the @{Shyne "+="} button on the top right.


@{b}HLH@{ub}'s buffer is used to hold URLs which have been cut or copied from the Main Window.


It also can hold URLs which have been grabbed via the @{"QuickGrab" Link "toolbar" 20} button
or the ARexx command 'AddLink'.


Multiselect is supported when choosing URLs in the buffer window.


After selecting at least one URL in the buffer window, you can copy or move them into any group
you desire.


@{JCenter}

@{b}NOTE:@{ub} @{u} The buffer window @{b}does not@{ub} hold URLs which have been REMOVED! @{uu}

@{JLeft}

@EndNode "bufferwindow"


@Node "searchwindow" "Search an HLH hotlist"
@TOC "windows"


@{Shine "Search Window"}
@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Ignore Case"}@{LIndent 10}

Do not differentiate between upper and lower case characters@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Wildcards"}@{LIndent 10}

You can use standard AmigaDos wildcards to search your hotlist.@{Lindent 5}


@{Shyne "Only Whole Words"}@{LIndent 10}

Because it doesn't make sense to use wildcards when searching on whole words,
HLH will not even let you try it.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Search"}@{LIndent 10}

HLH will search every URL for a match on names and links.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Next / Prev"}@{LIndent 10}

allow you to walk through all the URLs that HLH has identified as a match.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Clear"}@{LIndent 10}

Clear the search window.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Follow"}@{LIndent 10}

will tell the current browser to go to this link!@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Copy"}@{LIndent 10}

will copy the URL to the selected group.
@{LIndent 15}

If no group is opened HLH will place the URL in the @{"buffer" Link "bufferwindow"} (which
works the same as the Grab button).@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Cancel"}@{LIndent 10}

Cancel the search and close the window.@{LIndent 5}


@EndNode "searchwindow"


@Node "sort" "Sort an HLH hotlist"
@TOC "main"


@{Shine "Sort"}
@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Group"}@{LIndent 10}

When a group has been opened HLH displays the URLs within this group.@{LIndent 15}

All URLs in this group will be sorted.@{LIndent 5}


@{Shyne "Groups"}@{LIndent 10}

If no group is selected, HLH will sort only the 'main' groups.@{LIndent 15}

When a group has been selected, HLH will sort the subgroups
one level deeper than the selected group. Note that you can Unselect a selected group
with another click on it.@{LIndent 5}
  
@EndNode "sort"

@Node "menu" "Use the right mouse button with HLH"
@TOC "usage"


@{Shine "Menu"}
@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "Project"}
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Reload"}@{Fhine "NEW"}
@{LIndent 15}

Will reload the currently defined hotlist.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Open"}@{Fhine "NEW"}
@{LIndent 15}

To open a new hotlist from a file selector.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Save"}
@{LIndent 15}

Save your hotlist by overwriting the last loaded hotlist.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Save As..."}@{Fhine "NEW"}
@{LIndent 15}

Save your hotlist under a new name, via file requester.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Print"}@{Fhine "NEW"}
@{LIndent 15}

Output your hotlist to PRT:
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "About"}
@{LIndent 15}

Will open an Amiga requester containing information about @{b}HotListHandler@{ub}.
This will look friendlier after you have registered ;)
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Quit"}
@{LIndent 15}

Will quit @{b}HLH@{ub}.
@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "Settings"}
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Browser Type>>"}
@{LIndent 15}

Using the menu you can set the browser type so @{b}HLH@{ub} knows which command it has to use.
See @{"Browsers" Link "browsers"} for the list of browsers HLH supports.

Note that @{b}HLH@{ub} default settings are for AWeb.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Close on Follow"}
@{LIndent 15}

Toggle this on or off. When checked the @{b}HLH@{ub} Main Window will close after a URL is
double-clicked.
@{LIndent 10}

@{Fhyne "Active to Front"}@{Fhine "NEW"}
@{LIndent 15}

Toggle this on to cause the active window to come to the front of your screen.
@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "PubScreen"}
@{LIndent 10}

Choosing 'PubScreen' from the menu will present a submenu which includes all available pubscreens.
It allows you to pick the public screen you want @{b}HLH@{ub} to jump to.


This way you won't have to quit and restart @{b}HLH@{ub} when you start and stop your browser.
You can modify your hotlist and then run AWeb, or vica versa.
@{Line}This can also be handy when you are reading news or email.


@LIndent 0}

@EndNode "menu"


@NODE "tooltype" "How to Setup HLH"
@TOC "main"


@{Shine "Tooltypes & Arguments"}


@{Fhine "NEW"} - Highlighted items are - @{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 5}


HOTLIST=<path & name>@{LIndent 10}

Default = AmiTCP:AWeb/aweb.hotlist@{LIndent 5}


PUBSCREEN=<name>@{LIndent 10}

Default = AWeb@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "TOPEDGE=<number>"}@{LIndent 10}

Default = 0

The top of the HLH toolbar.@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "LEFTEDGE=<number>"}@{LIndent 10}

Default =

The left edge of HLH's toolbar.@{LIndent 5}


BROWSER=<number>@{LIndent 10}

Default=1 = AWeb@{LIndent 20}

2 = IBrowse

3 = Voyager

4 = AMosaic

@{Fhine "5 = Voyager-NG"}
@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "OPENWINDOW=<on/off>"}@{LIndent 10}

Default = OFF

Open the Main Window upon startup.

@EndNode "tooltype"




@NODE "bugs" "Problem?"
@TOC "MAIN"


@{Shine "Unknown Bugs"}

@{JLeft}

There must be an error somewhere!


But nothing has been found (or at least reported) yet!


See @{"Browsers" Link "browsers"} if you find that some features do not work for you.


Please write me, @{"Robert Nienkemper" Link "author"}, if you find a bug.
@{Line}I am happy to answer questions and I enjoy receiving comments and suggestions.


 - Robert

@EndNode "bugs"


@NODE "history" "An overview of HLH"
@TOC "MAIN"


@{Shine "History"}


@{JLeft}
@{u} Version 1.10 @{uu}

  - Second public release. (March, 1997)
@{LIndent 5}


@{Fhine "NEW"}@{LIndent 10}

· Created a Search function

· Added an ARexx port

· Added ToolTypes to provide Toolbar Positioning, Browser Selection, and OpenMainWindow.

· Implemented Sorting functions.

· Added a button to walk through Groups and Subgroups.

· Added support for multiple hotlists.

· Print a Hotlist.

· Read and write the "HIDE" tag when dealing with AWeb hotlists.

· Click to Unselect implemented.
@{LIndent 5}


Well, @{b}HLH@{ub} does everything I want, and most of what users and testers have asked for.
A few more improvements are planned.


Not many users have registered, so suggestions are dropping off : (

Therefore, the next release will probably be crippled.
@{LIndent 0}



@{u} Version 1.00 @{uu}

  - First public release (December, 1996)@{LIndent 5}

@{LIndent 0}


See @{"Future" Link "todo"} for planned additions to @{b}HLH@{ub}

@{LIndent 0}

@EndNode "history"


@Node "todo" "To Do in HotListHandler"


@{Shine "The Future"}
@{LIndent 5}


@{b}o@{ub} Sort Button improvements?


@{b}o@{ub} Keyboard shortcuts for the buttons


@{b}o@{ub} Smart Browser Port Recognition on Startup


@{b}o@{ub} Smart Browser Port Recognition to communicate with the browser while running.


@{b}o@{ub} Auto Close/Jump when current pubscreen tries to close.


@{b}o@{ub} Automatically open the Edit Window from a double-click in the Main Window if no browser is running.



@{b}o@{ub} Implement other @{"user suggestions" Link "author"}.
@{LIndent 0}


@EndNode "todo"


